&gt; How to open url with ntl auth or login, pass? Thanks &lt;br/&gt;
&gt; 1. Oh sorry, ntl is NTLM 2. Server authenticate me &quot;transparently&quot;

I will assume the user is authenticated against an AD domain. 

First - the [NTLM](https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/cc236621.aspx) protocol is not so simple as e.g. basic authentication. It is a multiple-step protocol involving some system/user specific data. Client and server need to exchange a few challenge/answer data in a Negotiation HTTP header.

I&#39;d suggest to use an out-of-box library; e.g [go-ntlmssp](https://github.com/Azure/go-ntlmssp) or [gokrb5](https://github.com/jcmturner/gokrb5). 

Note: when using SPNEGO (NTLM over HTTP) authentication, depending on the AD settings, if a user/service principal has too many roles, the Negotiation HTTP header may get VERY large. If you have any default limit for HTTP headers, you may watch if you don&#39;t reach the limit.

